The Indomitable Tinubu Support Organisation has said the presidential hopeful, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, will ensure a united and prosperous country if elected as the next president of Nigeria. The Director-General, ITSO, Abdoulbaq Balogun disclosed this in a statement on Wednesday, during a three-day retreat held by the group in Topo, Badagry. He said, “This timely retreat was organised for key members of 21 directorates to ensure they advocate rightly in their different communities not just to galvanise support for Asiwaju Tinubu but also to enrich their knowledge in political consultation and participatory democracy. “It is trite and common belief that, with Tinubu in the saddle, a secured, united and prosperous Nigeria is on the horizon. “As you can see, our members are drawn from all over the country and the diaspora, this retreat, with the ensuing campaigns will refresh our minds and enable us articulate a common strategy for the actualisation of our leader, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu’s presidential ambition. “The participating members were elated that they have been empowered and well equipped with useful knowledge to deliver the tasks ahead and collaborate with other individuals, socio-political groups and corporate organisations for the imminent economic renaissance, progressive political climate and social integration to be engender with the birth of Asiwaju Tinubu’s presidency from May 29, 2023.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com